WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:17.166
There's nothing left between us.

2
00:00:17.250 --> 00:00:19.875
The only way I'll be leaving you

3
00:00:19.958 --> 00:00:23.583
is the day they put me
in a coffin and bury me.

4
00:00:23.666 --> 00:00:25.375
Ma'am! Joyce!

5
00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:27.125
Mpume!

6
00:00:27.750 --> 00:00:30.583
Mr. Gomora!

7
00:00:30.666 --> 00:00:31.958
Mrs. Gomora.

8
00:00:37.083 --> 00:00:38.500
Doctor.

9
00:00:40.666 --> 00:00:43.291
Unfortunately. he hasn't woken up.

10
00:00:49.458 --> 00:00:50.500
Um…

11
00:00:51.416 --> 00:00:53.125
Hold on please.

12
00:00:53.708 --> 00:00:57.125
What are you saying to me?
Do you mean my husband won't make it?

13
00:00:58.208 --> 00:00:59.666
-No.
-Is my husband dead?

14
00:01:00.166 --> 00:01:02.291
No. no. no. Uh…

15
00:01:02.875 --> 00:01:05.458
He's alive and he's stable for now.

16
00:01:05.541 --> 00:01:08.166
Be that as it may.

17
00:01:08.250 --> 00:01:12.208
it's evident that Mr. Gomora
ingested poison.

18
00:01:15.875 --> 00:01:17.208
Poison?

19
00:01:17.291 --> 00:01:20.375
We were able to pump it
out of his stomach.

20
00:01:20.958 --> 00:01:21.958
Wow.

21
00:01:22.833 --> 00:01:24.791
This is shocking news.

22
00:01:24.875 --> 00:01:27.000
How can Jonasi do this to us?

23
00:01:27.083 --> 00:01:28.833
We have children together.

24
00:01:28.916 --> 00:01:32.750
Mrs. Gomora. do you suspect
that it's self-induced?

25
00:01:34.041 --> 00:01:36.000
I don't know what to say.

26
00:01:37.541 --> 00:01:41.875
Doctor. what I do know is that
lately we have been having issues.

27
00:01:42.416 --> 00:01:44.375
But suicide?

28
00:01:44.458 --> 00:01:45.458
Wow.

29
00:01:46.541 --> 00:01:47.916
I don't know.

30
00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:49.125
Let me get back to work.

31
00:01:49.208 --> 00:01:51.208
I'll keep you updated on everything.

32
00:01:51.291 --> 00:01:52.666
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

33
00:02:25.166 --> 00:02:26.375
Dad. what happened to our picture?

34
00:02:26.458 --> 00:02:29.208
The world does not revolve around you.

35
00:02:29.291 --> 00:02:31.958
You need to stop
behaving like this. Okay?

36
00:02:48.541 --> 00:02:49.583
Mom.

37
00:02:50.750 --> 00:02:52.916
Were your test results positive?

38
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:54.666
Mm-hmm.

39
00:03:06.375 --> 00:03:08.166
Maybe I should've married Magesh.

40
00:03:09.541 --> 00:03:10.541
I know. right?

41
00:03:49.333 --> 00:03:50.416
Brother.

42
00:03:51.583 --> 00:03:52.625
Brother.

43
00:03:54.458 --> 00:03:55.500
Hey.

44
00:03:56.916 --> 00:03:57.958
You're awake?

45
00:03:58.625 --> 00:04:00.375
Yeah. Where am I?

46
00:04:00.458 --> 00:04:01.458
Hospital.

47
00:04:01.541 --> 00:04:03.250
-You're going to be fine. Brother.
-Hospital?

48
00:04:03.333 --> 00:04:05.375
In fact. let me call the doctor.

49
00:04:07.416 --> 00:04:08.500
Doctor!

50
00:04:11.875 --> 00:04:13.083
Mr. Gomora.

51
00:04:14.083 --> 00:04:15.791
Oh. I'm glad to see that you're awake.

52
00:04:16.375 --> 00:04:17.583
What happened to me?

53
00:04:17.666 --> 00:04:20.625
Unfortunately. Mr. Gomora…

54
00:04:22.541 --> 00:04:25.250
you had a mild heart attack.

55
00:04:25.333 --> 00:04:28.000
Today. we stick to the same story.

56
00:04:28.083 --> 00:04:30.708
My husband had a heart attack.

57
00:04:31.875 --> 00:04:33.500
We're taking this to the grave.

58
00:04:36.750 --> 00:04:38.333
Mrs. Gomora. you arrived just in time.

59
00:04:38.416 --> 00:04:39.625
Joyce.

60
00:04:40.208 --> 00:04:42.375
You frightened us.

61
00:04:42.958 --> 00:04:45.833
How soon can we take my husband home?

62
00:04:45.916 --> 00:04:47.916
-Home?
-I want to go home. Brother.

63
00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:49.541
You know I hate hospitals.

64
00:04:49.625 --> 00:04:52.250
If I can request
for Mr. Gomora to get some rest.

65
00:04:52.333 --> 00:04:53.750
We still need to run a few more tests.

66
00:04:54.500 --> 00:04:55.916
Then we'll take it from there.

67
00:05:00.833 --> 00:05:01.916
Jo.

68
00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:03.083
Are you okay?

69
00:05:03.166 --> 00:05:04.708
Yes. I'm okay.

70
00:05:04.791 --> 00:05:08.083
Don't worry about anything else.
You'll be okay.

71
00:05:12.958 --> 00:05:16.958
What are your thoughts
or your views on beneficial ownership?

72
00:05:18.125 --> 00:05:19.666
Uh. just… just give me a second.

73
00:05:19.750 --> 00:05:22.750
Jane. are the kids okay?

74
00:05:23.583 --> 00:05:25.625
I'm in an interview. I'll call you later.

75
00:05:26.166 --> 00:05:28.333
I'm in an interview. I'll call you.

76
00:05:28.416 --> 00:05:29.416
Okay. fine.

77
00:05:32.208 --> 00:05:33.708
I'm… I'm so sorry about that.

78
00:05:34.291 --> 00:05:35.583
Beneficial ownership?

79
00:05:37.250 --> 00:05:42.250
Um. to… to be honest.
I hadn't really studied the act in depth.

80
00:05:45.333 --> 00:05:46.583
I see.

81
00:05:47.541 --> 00:05:49.625
That'll be all for now.
We'll keep in touch.

82
00:05:49.708 --> 00:05:51.750
Thank you. I… I look forward to it.

83
00:05:52.916 --> 00:05:54.333
Fuck.

84
00:05:54.416 --> 00:05:56.250
There's no way I'm getting that job.

85
00:05:56.333 --> 00:05:58.291
But you know what? It's fine.

86
00:05:58.375 --> 00:05:59.375
Minor setback.

87
00:05:59.458 --> 00:06:01.916
It doesn't change the fact
that I'm getting the hell away from here.

88
00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:04.750
Friend. how will you survive
with two kids without a job?

89
00:06:07.250 --> 00:06:09.916
Let's drink. Let's drink.

90
00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:13.458
Mmm. Mmm. This is really good.

91
00:06:14.083 --> 00:06:16.625
Ooh.

92
00:06:26.458 --> 00:06:29.958
Let me rest on the couch.

93
00:06:30.750 --> 00:06:32.041
Maybe I should've stayed

94
00:06:32.125 --> 00:06:34.708
-longer at the hospital.
-Mm-mmm.

95
00:06:34.791 --> 00:06:40.375
Imagine if word got out
that the CEO was hospitalized.

96
00:06:40.458 --> 00:06:43.666
-That would surely tank the share price.
-Mmm.

97
00:06:43.750 --> 00:06:45.750
You're fine here at home.

98
00:06:45.833 --> 00:06:47.541
Besides. you're a strong man.

99
00:06:47.625 --> 00:06:50.458
-Wow.
-You know it's true. You're a man.

100
00:06:50.541 --> 00:06:52.583
-Come on.
-This is nothing to you.

101
00:06:53.166 --> 00:06:54.416
All right.

102
00:06:54.500 --> 00:06:55.833
One more thing.

103
00:06:56.875 --> 00:07:00.291
I want to apologize
for almost leaving you guys.

104
00:07:00.375 --> 00:07:01.375
Hmm.

105
00:07:01.875 --> 00:07:04.375
And I want you to know
that I'm not going anywhere.

106
00:07:04.458 --> 00:07:06.416
I'm here to stay.

107
00:07:06.500 --> 00:07:09.541
-I promise.
-Sleep. love.

108
00:07:10.125 --> 00:07:13.125
-Mmm.
-We thank the Lord

109
00:07:13.791 --> 00:07:15.375
for that. my love.

110
00:07:20.208 --> 00:07:23.500
Let me give you your medication
before I leave.

111
00:07:23.583 --> 00:07:25.541
I had already taken those.

112
00:07:26.333 --> 00:07:27.791
These are antibiotics.

113
00:07:27.875 --> 00:07:31.083
You infected us with an STI.

114
00:07:31.166 --> 00:07:32.625
All of us.

115
00:07:32.708 --> 00:07:35.208
Take your medication and end all of this.

116
00:07:36.458 --> 00:07:38.791
Leave them on the table.
I'll take them later.

117
00:07:38.875 --> 00:07:40.708
I'll come check on you.

118
00:07:40.791 --> 00:07:43.416
It's you and I forever.

119
00:07:43.500 --> 00:07:45.458
Until death do us apart.

120
00:07:45.541 --> 00:07:48.458
Jonasi and Joyce.

121
00:07:55.708 --> 00:07:56.708
Mom?

122
00:07:58.166 --> 00:07:59.250
Hey.

123
00:08:00.333 --> 00:08:05.333
Mom. I don't think you should be drinking
alcohol while you're on medication.

124
00:08:06.041 --> 00:08:07.583
Oh. Sarah. my child.

125
00:08:08.166 --> 00:08:10.666
I know. but I have so many problems.
Good lord.

126
00:08:10.750 --> 00:08:13.583
Someone almost died from a heart attack

127
00:08:13.666 --> 00:08:15.166
and no one even bothered
to tell me about it.

128
00:08:15.250 --> 00:08:18.416
-What's going on?
-I forgot to call you. I'm sorry. Essie.

129
00:08:18.500 --> 00:08:20.791
The problem is Jonasi.
He was supposed to call me.

130
00:08:20.875 --> 00:08:23.791
He only remembers me
when his wives deny him what he wants.

131
00:08:23.875 --> 00:08:25.458
-He always wants--
-Stop.

132
00:08:26.708 --> 00:08:29.875
No. don't stress about it.

133
00:08:29.958 --> 00:08:32.458
You don't have to hide the truth.
I know my dad is wicked.

134
00:08:32.541 --> 00:08:34.625
Wicked is an understatement.

135
00:08:35.125 --> 00:08:36.625
Your father is useless.

136
00:08:36.708 --> 00:08:39.083
Him and that idiot wife of his.

137
00:08:39.166 --> 00:08:41.625
Don't stress about people
who don't care about you. Mom.

138
00:08:41.708 --> 00:08:44.291
You're right. my baby.
I really don't care.

139
00:08:44.375 --> 00:08:46.833
From now on.
I'm living my life and that's it.

140
00:08:48.625 --> 00:08:49.708
Tholakele?

141
00:08:49.791 --> 00:08:51.416
Um…

142
00:08:51.500 --> 00:08:52.500
Is that your new girlfriend?

143
00:08:53.083 --> 00:08:55.583
-Huh?
-Magesh. relax.

144
00:08:56.166 --> 00:08:59.375
The secret is out. Everyone is
living their lives. Live yours too.

145
00:08:59.958 --> 00:09:02.125
-Yeah. her name's Tholakele.
-Mmm.

146
00:09:02.791 --> 00:09:04.750
She's a chartered accountant.

147
00:09:04.833 --> 00:09:06.541
Oh. wow.

148
00:09:06.625 --> 00:09:10.166
She's a wonderful woman.
I see a future with her.

149
00:09:10.250 --> 00:09:12.416
Oh. wow. Magesh.

150
00:09:12.500 --> 00:09:14.916
You've found the one. hey.

151
00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:17.166
Pick up the phone before she dumps you.

152
00:09:19.583 --> 00:09:20.916
Hello. my size.

153
00:09:21.625 --> 00:09:23.333
How are you?

154
00:09:23.416 --> 00:09:25.250
Oh. well.

155
00:09:29.958 --> 00:09:31.000
Joy-Joy!

156
00:09:37.916 --> 00:09:38.916
Oh.

157
00:09:40.041 --> 00:09:41.125
It's you.

158
00:09:45.750 --> 00:09:46.958
You're drinking my alcohol.

159
00:09:51.250 --> 00:09:56.291
Listen. when you're done
destressing with my alcohol.

160
00:09:56.875 --> 00:09:59.125
get me some water from the kitchen.

161
00:10:12.041 --> 00:10:13.666
Why don't you go and get it yourself?

162
00:10:18.125 --> 00:10:19.125
I beg your pardon?

163
00:10:19.208 --> 00:10:20.833
I said get your own water!

164
00:10:22.458 --> 00:10:23.875
Who are you talking to like that?

165
00:10:26.708 --> 00:10:27.708
Huh?

166
00:10:29.166 --> 00:10:30.208
You've grown a pair.

167
00:10:30.291 --> 00:10:32.458
I'm still your father!

168
00:10:33.541 --> 00:10:34.791
You don't have any balls.

169
00:10:34.875 --> 00:10:36.916
You're still scared of girls.

170
00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:38.625
You're just a weakling!

171
00:10:44.583 --> 00:10:46.541
It would really be great if you could do

172
00:10:46.625 --> 00:10:48.375
an immediate transfer into this account.

173
00:10:59.875 --> 00:11:02.583
We're going to need Mr. Gomora
to authorize this transfer.

174
00:11:02.666 --> 00:11:04.875
Have you forgotten
that Mr. Gomora is my husband

175
00:11:04.958 --> 00:11:06.750
and I have every right to this account?

176
00:11:06.833 --> 00:11:08.166
It's a huge sum of money.

177
00:11:08.250 --> 00:11:10.791
As a primary account holder.
we need him to sign.

178
00:11:10.875 --> 00:11:12.666
But didn't I just tell you
that he's in hospital?

179
00:11:13.541 --> 00:11:16.958
How's about I drive to him
and have him sign there?

180
00:11:17.041 --> 00:11:20.208
How's about I wheel him in here
along with his life support

181
00:11:20.291 --> 00:11:22.041
for the whole damn world to see?

182
00:11:22.125 --> 00:11:23.833
I'm simply following protocol.

183
00:11:23.916 --> 00:11:25.000
Really?

184
00:11:26.208 --> 00:11:28.416
You know what? It's fine.

185
00:11:28.500 --> 00:11:31.208
I'll have him call you.
confirm the transfer.

186
00:11:31.291 --> 00:11:33.208
while praying to God
that I don't lose my husband.

187
00:11:36.375 --> 00:11:37.375
Mrs. Gomora. please wait.

188
00:11:38.833 --> 00:11:41.791
I'll transfer the money.
and I'll sort it out with Mr. Gomora.

189
00:11:41.875 --> 00:11:44.916
The money should reflect in about an hour.

190
00:11:46.791 --> 00:11:47.791
Thank you.

191
00:11:49.958 --> 00:11:51.125
Joyce.

192
00:11:54.250 --> 00:11:55.250
Joyce!

193
00:11:57.291 --> 00:11:59.625
This is Joyce Gomora. Leave a message.

194
00:12:00.500 --> 00:12:01.791
Hello. Essie here.

195
00:12:01.875 --> 00:12:03.208
-I can't take your call right now.
-Joyce!

196
00:12:03.291 --> 00:12:06.000
Hi. this is Matipa. I'm not available.

197
00:12:06.083 --> 00:12:07.958
Our marriage is built on a lie.

198
00:12:08.041 --> 00:12:10.125
You deceived me into believing
I was your second wife.

199
00:12:10.208 --> 00:12:11.250
Hello. this is Lindani.

200
00:12:11.333 --> 00:12:13.208
-I'll get back to you.
-I'm done being your toilet!

201
00:12:13.291 --> 00:12:14.541
-Let go of my mother. you bastard!
-I hate you.

202
00:12:14.625 --> 00:12:17.291
All the love I had for you…

203
00:12:32.125 --> 00:12:33.333
Where are you going?

204
00:12:34.666 --> 00:12:35.875
Off to see your sugar daddy?

205
00:12:41.958 --> 00:12:43.375
What are you doing here. Menzi?

206
00:12:45.750 --> 00:12:49.083
Tell me something. Lindani.
What's wrong with you?

207
00:12:50.833 --> 00:12:53.875
You know. I don't expect you
to understand my situation.

208
00:12:53.958 --> 00:12:56.708
You're right. I don't understand
this shit that you're doing.

209
00:13:01.958 --> 00:13:03.416
You know. I wanted to love you.

210
00:13:05.666 --> 00:13:07.500
I wanted to…

211
00:13:07.583 --> 00:13:08.625
I wanted to…

212
00:13:09.916 --> 00:13:11.333
I wanted to marry you.

213
00:13:12.916 --> 00:13:14.375
Make you my wife.

214
00:13:14.458 --> 00:13:15.583
Make me your wife?

215
00:13:16.208 --> 00:13:17.875
Menzi. you and I never dated.

216
00:13:17.958 --> 00:13:20.250
Nothing has ever happened between us.

217
00:13:22.083 --> 00:13:23.208
What? Is he giving you money?

218
00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:25.541
Huh? Do you want money?

219
00:13:25.625 --> 00:13:28.541
I'll give you anything you want.
Do you hear me?

220
00:13:28.625 --> 00:13:32.166
Whatever you want.
I'll give you anything you want.

221
00:13:32.250 --> 00:13:33.750
Let me go. Menzi. Are you mad?

222
00:13:33.833 --> 00:13:35.416
Go to hell. Gosh.

223
00:13:35.500 --> 00:13:37.375
Listen here. you slut.
I'm still talking to you.

224
00:13:40.833 --> 00:13:42.041
How much is he giving you?

225
00:13:43.166 --> 00:13:44.500
Let me go.

226
00:13:59.416 --> 00:14:03.333
I see you decided
not to take your medication.

227
00:14:03.416 --> 00:14:04.416
Where have you been?

228
00:14:05.041 --> 00:14:06.041
Excuse me?

229
00:14:06.125 --> 00:14:07.750
You left me here unattended.

230
00:14:08.916 --> 00:14:10.416
You know I just came
out of hospital. right?

231
00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:12.041
Oh. whatever.

232
00:14:12.125 --> 00:14:14.250
-Joyce.
-Oh. come on now.

233
00:14:14.333 --> 00:14:15.750
Don't walk away from me
while I'm talking to you.

234
00:14:15.833 --> 00:14:17.166
Oh. please. Stop it.

235
00:14:17.250 --> 00:14:18.375
-My gosh.
-Excuse me.

236
00:14:19.625 --> 00:14:21.041
Have you forgotten I'm your husband?

237
00:14:22.875 --> 00:14:24.416
You're my husband?

238
00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:26.416
You're my husband only when it suits you.

239
00:14:27.083 --> 00:14:29.083
You left me here alone unattended.

240
00:14:30.041 --> 00:14:31.833
You're out gallivanting? Huh?

241
00:14:31.916 --> 00:14:34.416
-Are you a lady of the streets now?
-Lady of the streets?

242
00:14:34.500 --> 00:14:37.583
I'm asking you.
what else did you want from me?

243
00:14:37.666 --> 00:14:39.916
Did you want me to put you on my back?

244
00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:42.041
Or put me on my chest and breastfeed you?

245
00:14:42.125 --> 00:14:43.833
That would've been a start.

246
00:14:43.916 --> 00:14:45.333
Please.

247
00:14:45.916 --> 00:14:47.375
You're not a child.

248
00:14:47.458 --> 00:14:49.041
Neither are you.

249
00:14:50.333 --> 00:14:51.333
But here you are.

250
00:14:52.833 --> 00:14:54.750
I take care of you.

251
00:14:54.833 --> 00:14:58.583
Even these clothes you're wearing.
I'm the one that bought them for you.

252
00:14:58.666 --> 00:15:00.750
But have you ever heard me complain?
Have you ever--

253
00:15:00.833 --> 00:15:04.833
As if you qualify to complain.

254
00:15:05.833 --> 00:15:07.708
Gomora. listen.

255
00:15:08.375 --> 00:15:11.000
Even on your greatest days.

256
00:15:11.083 --> 00:15:15.791
don't ever forget that I made you.

257
00:15:15.875 --> 00:15:16.875
Ah.

258
00:15:16.958 --> 00:15:19.250
-My father gave you an opportunity.
-Oh?

259
00:15:19.333 --> 00:15:22.750
Gave you a seat at the table
when all you were worth

260
00:15:22.833 --> 00:15:25.541
was nothing but crumbs off a dog's plate.

261
00:15:25.625 --> 00:15:29.875
We saved you from Soweto
and made you who you are.

262
00:15:29.958 --> 00:15:33.333
You would still be trash in Soweto
if we didn't rescue you.

